=======================================================

Working on Container

10. to see the list if all running container
    docker conrainer ls

11. to see the list of running and stopped container
    docker ps -a

12. To start a container
    docker start contaner_name/id

13. To stop a container
    docker stop container_name/id

14. To restart a container
    docker restart container_name/id
    docker restart -t 10 container_name/id #(to restart after 10 seconds)

15. To delete/remove a stopped container
    docker rm container_name/id

16. To delete/remove a running container
    docker rm -f container_name/id
    f: stands for file system

17. to stop all container which are running
    docker stop $(docker ps -aq)

18. To restart all containers
    docker restart $(docker ps -aq)

19. To remove all stopped container
    docker rm $(docker ps -aq)

20. To remove all container (running and stopped)
    docker rm -f $(docker ps -aq)

21. to see the logs generated by a container
    docker logs container_name/id

22. To see the ports used by a container
    docker port container_name/id

23. to get detailes info about a container
    docker inspect container_name/id

24. To go into the shell of a running container which is moved into backgrouund
    docker attach container_name/id

25. to execute any command in a container
    docker exec -it container_name/id command
    eg: to launch the bash shell in a container
    docker exec -it container_name/id bash

26. To create a container from a docker image (IMP)
    docker run image_name

